==English==

===Etymology===
While the first attestation of the term in English dates to 1628, it is uncertain how "Cape Horn" entered the English language.
Ultimately, the name derives from the {{etyl|nl}} ''[[kaap|Kaap]] {{w|Hoorn}}'', named after the hometown and flagship of {{w|Willem Schouten}}, who became the first Englishman to sail from the cape to the Pacific Ocean in 1616.

